This discipline can be overlooked. I find it most useful when a planar pull goes wrong.<br>
We were in Hate and I was on main assist /tagging duties and the monk said TAG. So i shot, well turns out they hit the wrong button. 3 clerics 3 kiras and a spite golem charged me. I had the Spite golem targeted and when all the mobs were at me i let the discipline fly. hehe SPAM!!!!  well anyway, my point is this. I was able to buy the enchanters enough time to mez the mobs and the cleric was able to heal me without getting charged, because the mobs that were not mez'd were still being hit by me and I had their agro.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mighty Strike: (aka A$$ whopping disc)<br>
I use this one for fun mainly, like when i'm dueling or just doing EXP and I'll tell the cleric to let me get it off before he starts to cast CH.. Very fun.<br>
But the most useful use for it is when your doing some big mob that CH's and/or Gates and you are berserk. Pop this discipline and you'll stun him to hell and back.<br>
<br>
<br>
Precision:<br>
Use on melee fights where I'm not the main tank. If I'm just there for damage this discipline is the best thing I can use.  Just don't taunt.</font><P>
